HEADWORD: Allision
<hw>Al*li"sion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>allisio</ets>, fr. <ets>allidere</ets>, to strike or dash against;
<ets>ad</ets> + <ets>laedere</ets> to dash against.]</ety> <def>The act
of dashing against, or striking upon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The boisterous <qex>allision</qex> of the sea.</q>
<rj><qau>Woodward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alliteral</ent>⟦br⟧
